      "Title": "Wolfgang.AuditTrail.AuditingDbContext",
      "Summary": "<p sourcefile=\"api/Wolfgang.AuditTrail.AuditingDbContext.yml\" sourcestartlinenumber=\"1\">Base <xref href=\"Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> that writes audit rows atomically with every\n<xref href=\"Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext.SaveChanges\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref> / <xref href=\"Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext.SaveChangesAsync(System.Threading.CancellationToken)\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\ncall. Derive your application's context from this instead of <xref href=\"Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext\" data-throw-if-not-resolved=\"false\"></xref>\nand continue calling <code>SaveChangesAsync</code> as usual — audit capture happens\ntransparently in the same transaction.</p>\n"
    },
